Your package hex-a-hop failed to build from source in current rawhide.
http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=12822806
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_24_Mass_Rebuild

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase

Created attachment 1137451 Patch to fix the FTBFS
This FTBFS is caused by the package mixing "%doc <relative path>" and direct doc installation. This is not supported in newer version of rpm, anymore.
This patch in the attachment (against git/master) changes the package to directly install all doc-files into %{_pkgdocdir}. Additionally, the patch also addresses RHBZ#1318756.
Unless somebody objects, I indent to apply this patch in near future.
